FBIS3-14537 "drnes060_k_94004" FBIS-NES-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 IRAQ UN Vehicle Attacked at Checkpoint NC2803180494 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan in Arabic 1500 GMT 28 Mar 94 NC2803180494 (Clandestine) Voice of the People of Kurdistan in Arabic 1500 GMT 28 Mar 94 Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] A UN vehicle was the target of an attack by agents of the Iraqi regime at the [name indistinct] checkpoint yesterday as the vehicle was traveling from Irbil to Mosul. It was carrying four people, two of them UN policemen. An employee of the IRC [abbreviation given in English--International Red Cross] Organization named [words indistinct] told KURDISTAN NWAY newspaper that nine armed men opened fire at the vehicle at the Iraqi regime's checkpoint, seriously wounding the passengers. Eyewitnesses said that the nine armed men, who were dressed in Kurdish costumes, fled to the nearby Iraqi regime camps.
